    "NMR spectroscopy and fluorescence-based methods can provide relevant information but are time consuming, and so far the dynamic information is not well captured in public databases.",
    "MD simulations can be performed, starting from experimental structures, and letting them evolve in time using a force field that describes the molecular potential energy surface.",
    "Typically, periods of nanoseconds to microseconds can be achieved for individual systems, depending on system size.",
    "MD traces allow the analysis of small-range structural fluctuations of the protein-ligand complex, but in some cases large-scale rare events can be observed (Fig. 3).",
    "In existing DD software these events are mostly neglected."
